spec: multiprocessing_extra124
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(multiprocessing)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html — Python multiprocessing module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/multiprocessing/context.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec covers: wave 255 theme — multiprocessing.Lock, Semaphore, and related synchronization class identity. NEW in extra124: multiprocessing.Lock.__class__.__name__=='method' (Lock is a bound method of the default context, not a class); multiprocessing.Semaphore.__class__.__name__=='method'; multiprocessing.RLock.__class__.__name__=='method'; multiprocessing.Barrier.__class__.__name__=='method'; multiprocessing.Condition.__class__.__name__=='method'; multiprocessing.Event.__class__.__name__=='method'; multiprocessing.Manager.__class__.__name__=='method'; multiprocessing.Value.__class__.__name__=='method'; all share __module__=='multiprocessing.context'; multiprocessing.Lock.__qualname__=='BaseContext.Lock' (len=16); multiprocessing.Semaphore.__qualname__=='BaseContext.Semaphore' (len=21); multiprocessing.RLock.__qualname__=='BaseContext.RLock' (len=17); multiprocessing.Barrier.__qualname__=='BaseContext.Barrier' (len=19); multiprocessing.Condition.__qualname__=='BaseContext.Condition' (len=21, tied with Semaphore); multiprocessing.Event.__qualname__=='BaseContext.Event' (len=17, tied with RLock); multiprocessing.Manager.__qualname__=='BaseContext.Manager' (len=19, tied with Barrier); multiprocessing.Value.__qualname__=='BaseContext.Value' (len=17, tied with RLock and Event). All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "multiprocessing.Lock.__class__.__name__ == 'method'. Lock, Semaphore, RLock, etc. are NOT classes at the top-level multiprocessing namespace. They are bound methods of the default multiprocessing context (an instance of DefaultContext from Lib/multiprocessing/context.py). When called (e.g. multiprocessing.Lock()), they return instances of the appropriate synchronization class for the current start method. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "All synchronization factory methods have __qualname__ with 'BaseContext.' prefix (len=12). Lock.__qualname__='BaseContext.Lock' (len=16: 'BaseContext.'=12+'Lock'=4); Semaphore.__qualname__='BaseContext.Semaphore' (len=21: 'BaseContext.'=12+'Semaphore'=9); RLock.__qualname__='BaseContext.RLock' (len=17: 'BaseContext.'=12+'RLock'=5); Barrier.__qualname__='BaseContext.Barrier' (len=19: 'BaseContext.'=12+'Barrier'=7); Condition.__qualname__='BaseContext.Condition' (len=21: 'BaseContext.'=12+'Condition'=9, tied with Semaphore); Event.__qualname__='BaseContext.Event' (len=17: 'BaseContext.'=12+'Event'=5, tied with RLock); Manager.__qualname__='BaseContext.Manager' (len=19: 'BaseContext.'=12+'Manager'=7, tied with Barrier); Value.__qualname__='BaseContext.Value' (len=17: 'BaseContext.'=12+'Value'=5, tied with RLock and Event). Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

