invariant multiprocessing_extra124.all_sync_methods_share_module:
  description: "multiprocessing.Semaphore.__module__.__eq__('multiprocessing.context') returns True — all 8 multiprocessing synchronization factory methods (Lock, Semaphore, RLock, Barrier, Condition, Event, Manager, Value) share the same __module__=='multiprocessing.context' because they are all defined as methods on BaseContext in Lib/multiprocessing/context.py; the default multiprocessing context is an instance of DefaultContext (which inherits from BaseContext) and is created at module load time; all 8 methods are bound to this single DefaultContext instance; their class is 'method' (not 'function' or 'builtin_function_or_method'); __module__ is 'multiprocessing.context' (len=24: 'multiprocessing.'=16+'context'=8=24); NEW in extra124: first standalone Semaphore module invariant in mpsyncident124 namespace; wave 255; verified with Python 3.14.3"
  category: identity
